ENTRY            M1067   20260405   20260518   20260518       M145
SUBENT        M1067001   20260405   20260518   20260518       M145
BIB                 13         33
TITLE      Study of Activation of 186,188,189Re in (gamma,p)
            reactions.
AUTHOR     (M.V.Zheltonozhskaya,P.D.Remizov,A.P.Chernyaev,
            A.A.Kuzmenkov,V.D.Pupyshev)
REFERENCE  (J,PAN,88,1115,2025)
           #doi:10.1134/S106377882560191X
            English translation of YF,88,435,2025.
           (J,YF,88,435,2025)
           #doi:10.7868/S3034628225060013
INSTITUTE  (4RUSMOS)
FACILITY   (LINAC,4RUSRUS) Varian Trilogy medical linear electron
            accelerator of the Moscow Federal Medical Biological
            Center.
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Induced beta-delayed g-activity measured.
SAMPLE     Osmium targets with natural isotopic composition
            (184Os (0.018%), 186Os (1.59%), 187Os (1.64%),
            188Os (13.3%), 189Os (16.1%), 190Os (26.24%),
            and 192Os (41.1%)).
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Semiconductor spectrometers with Canberra and
            ORTEC ultrapure germanium detectors with detection
            efficiency of (15-40)%. The energy resolution of the
            of the spectrometers was 1.8-2.0 keV for the 1173
            and 1332 keV lines of 60Co.
MONITOR    (73-TA-181(G,N)73-TA-180,,SIG)
ANALYSIS   Gamma-quanta energy spectrum lines data.
            The gamma spectra were processed using the
            Winspectrum program.
COMMENT    The weighted average yields of (g,p) reactions at
            23 MeV bremsstrahlung on natural osmium were
            measured.
HISTORY    (20260405C) Data were compiled at the Russia MSU SINP
            CDFE by V.Varlamov.
ENDBIB              33
COMMON               1          3
EN-MAX
MEV
   23.0
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           40
SUBENT        M1067002   20260405   20260518   20260518       M145
BIB                  4         13
REACTION   (76-OS-0(G,X)75-RE-186,,SIG,,BRA)
            The bremsstrahlung spectrum-weighted average yield of
             reaction sum [187Os(g,p) + 188Os(g,np)]
            yield.
DECAY-DATA (75-RE-186,,DG,137.2)
            Data from text on page 1116 of PAN,88,1115,2025.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The error combines the errors in
            the measurement and processing of the gamma-ray
            spectra and the error in the value of the mass
            fraction of the 187Os and 188Os isotopes in the
            natural osmium mixture.
STATUS     (TABLE,,M.V.Zheltonozhskaya+,J,PAN,88,1115,2025)
            Data presented in Table 1.
